SIMPLE: destroyer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Destroyer
<hw>De*stroy"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>destruior</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who destroys, ruins,
kills, or desolates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Nav.)</fld> <def>a small fast warship used
primarily as an escort to larger vessels and typically armed with a
combination of 5-inch guns, torpedoes, depth charges, and missiles;
formerly identical to the <er>Torpedo-boat destroyer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Destruct</ent>⟦br⟧
